  "prompt": "What is the difference between studying in India and studying in any other place like the US/UK/Australia?",
  "response": "Here are key differences between studying in India and studying abroad:\n\nIndia:\n1. Lower cost of education\n2. Cultural familiarity\n3. Strong family support system\n4. Less international exposure\n5. Local language and cultural context\n6. Curriculum more theory-oriented\n7. Traditional teaching methods\n8. Less emphasis on practical skills\n9. Large student population\n10. Limited research opportunities\n\nAbroad (US/UK/Australia):\n1. Higher education costs\n2. International exposure\n3. Independent living experience\n4. Multicultural environment\n5. Advanced research facilities\n6. Practical, skill-based learning\n7. Modern teaching methodologies\n8. Industry-oriented curriculum\n9. Better global networking opportunities\n10. Cutting-edge technology access\n11. More interactive classroom environment\n12. Higher chances of internships\n13. Better career prospects\n14. English-medium instruction\n15. Potential work/immigration opportunities after graduation\n\nFactors to consider:\n- Personal financial capacity\n- Career goals\n- Academic interests\n- Long-term professional plans\n- Personal adaptability\n- Scholarships and funding options\n\nEach option has pros and cons, and the best choice depends on individual goals and circumstances.",
